This project is a vscode/cursor extension paired with a living program that will track copy/paste information, and will relay source infromation within an ide. Please refer to the official cursor and vscode docs for API requests concerning extension development.

VSCode Extension Api Documentation: 
VSCode Extension Samples: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-extension-samples

--------------------------------
------- Components ------------
--------------------------------

System Architecture 
 

Comp 1: IDE Extension: 

Extension for Visual Studio/Cursor 
Tracks edit by listening for onDidChangeTextDocument (https://code.visualstudio.com/api/references/vscode-api) 
Log: 
inserted text 
deleted text 
AI Generation 
Cursor emits events for AI completions. 
Ex) 
source: cursor_ai 
model: claude-3.7 
prompt: <prompt text> 
Pasted Code Detection(Using Clipboard Hook) 
Comp 2: Clipboard Monitor/Hook 

Background App on users machine that monitors clipboard events 
Example flow: 
User copies StackOverflow code 
↓ 
Clipboard listener records: 
   source_url 
   clipboard_hash 
↓ 
User pastes into IDE 
↓ 
Match pasted text to clipboard record 
Result: origin = stackoverflow.com/12345 

Component 3: AI API Proxy 

Hook Directly into AI Plugins through IDE 
Cursor Extension logs: 
prompt 
model 
response 
inserted code region 
IDE extension for Cursor/Copilot/inline completions inside the editor 
For: 
Cursor 

Copilot 



Component 4: Brower Extension 

Logs: 
prompt text 
response text 
model name 
URL 
copy event 
time 
Example:  
prompt = "write quicksort in python" 
model = gpt-4.1 
url = chat.openai.com 
copied = True 

Component 5: Behavior Analyzer 

Processes logs from the IDE extension, browser extension, clipboard monitor, and AI interaction logger. 
Reconstructs coding sessions from timestamped events. 
Identifies code origin, such as AI-generated, AI-modified, human-written, or external paste. 
Links prompts, responses, and inserted code to track AI-assisted coding flow. 
Extracts session features such as AI usage ratio, paste ratio, edit frequency, typing speed, and model usage. 
Classifies coding behavior, such as manual, AI-assisted, AI-heavy, or vibe coding. 
Outputs structured results for evaluation and visualization. 
Component 6: Visualization Dashboard 

Displays analysis results from the Behavior Analyzer. 
Shows coding timelines with prompts, responses, pastes, edits, and saves. 
Highlights code origin by line, such as human, AI-generated, AI-modified, or external. 
Visualizes key metrics such as AI usage, paste ratio, edit ratio, and model usage. 
Supports comparison across sessions, users, and AI tools. 
Generates charts and summaries for experiments and research reports. 
 

